      {
        "paragraph_index": 1,
        "text": "## Ranking\n| Rank | Metal ion | logK |\n|---|---|---:|\n| 1 | Hg²⁺ | 9.64 |\n| 2 | Cd²⁺ | 1.93 |\n| 3 | Pb²⁺ | 0.49 |\n\n\n**Hg²⁺ has by far the highest affinity** for thiocyanate/thiocyanic acid in SRD-46.\n\nThis ranking, **Hg²⁺ > Cd²⁺ > Pb²⁺**, is consistent with soft-acid/soft-base chemistry: **SCN⁻ is a soft donor ligand**, and **Hg²⁺** is the softest of the three metals, so it binds most strongly.\n\n*Source: NIST SRD-46 equilibrium network data for ligand_10092 (Hydrogen thiocyanate / thiocyanic acid), beta_def_812.*",
